This paper is likely to belong to the Computer Science sub-category of Cryptography and Security (cs.CR) as it deals with the issue of identifying scam ICOs, which is a security concern. Additionally, the paper mentions the use of natural language processing techniques, which suggests that it may also belong to the sub-categories of Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) and Information Retrieval (cs.IR). The use of supervised learning models further supports the possibility of it belonging to the sub-category of Machine Learning (cs.LG). Finally, the paper discusses the need for a reliable credit rating system, which could also place it in the sub-category of Software Engineering (cs.SE).
